WEBVTT

00:05.072 --> 00:06.739
SAM:
<i> Previously on</i> Aquarius...

00:06.741 --> 00:08.707
-I'm Charlie Manson.
-How do you know my name?

00:08.709 --> 00:10.042
GRACE: <i> My daughter, Emma,</i>
<i> she's gone.</i>

00:10.044 --> 00:13.245
If you can keep it quiet,
there are people who'd
appreciate it.

00:13.247 --> 00:14.079
Get my little girl back.

00:14.081 --> 00:16.081
What, are you afraid
of the cops?

00:16.283 --> 00:19.018
Relax.
I want him, not you.

00:19.020 --> 00:19.585
That Shafe kid.

00:19.587 --> 00:21.754
You volunteering to give him
the buzz cut?

00:21.756 --> 00:23.655
So wait. I report to you?

00:23.657 --> 00:25.591
Look, I didn't crack
some secret hippie code

00:25.593 --> 00:27.126
to tell you what
they're really saying.

00:27.128 --> 00:28.560
Name Manson ring a bell?

00:28.562 --> 00:29.294
Your husband was his lawyer.

00:29.296 --> 00:31.697
<i> I don't think this is about</i>
<i> Manson and your daughter.</i>

00:31.699 --> 00:33.098
<i> It's about Manson</i>
<i> and your husband.</i>

00:33.100 --> 00:35.701
-She's sweet,
that little Emma.
-(SIGHS)

00:35.803 --> 00:37.169
(BOTH GRUNT)

00:37.838 --> 00:39.071
Don't.

00:42.810 --> 00:44.910
GRACE: I don't understand how.

00:44.912 --> 00:47.246
-How?
-A knife, how.

00:47.248 --> 00:48.480
And you fought him? Why?

00:48.482 --> 00:53.118
I'm not gonna let some little
spic get (STAMMERING)
my watch, my wallet,

00:53.120 --> 00:55.554
SAM: How'd you
fight him off?

00:57.291 --> 00:58.657
The briefcase.

01:05.499 --> 01:05.798
What?

01:05.800 --> 01:10.769
Just thought there might be
scratch marks
from the struggle.

01:12.206 --> 01:14.640
What happened to your pants?

01:27.822 --> 01:30.489
Is there a reason
you're here, Detective?

01:30.825 --> 01:33.225
He knows who Emma's with.

01:33.994 --> 01:35.494
All right.

01:36.630 --> 01:38.597
Just tell me where.
I'll go pick her up.

01:38.599 --> 01:41.200
Name Charles Manson
ring a bell?

01:41.202 --> 01:44.970
-No.
-You sure?

01:47.641 --> 01:55.214
Well, that's... I knew him
years ago, but what does
this have to do...

01:55.216 --> 01:56.281
Emma's with him.

01:56.283 --> 01:57.916
What? Why?

01:57.918 --> 02:00.219
-He's your client.
-Ex-client.

02:00.221 --> 02:02.855
Has he contacted you?

02:05.059 --> 02:07.526
Grace, what the hell is this?

02:07.528 --> 02:11.330
-Just tell us everything.
-Us?

02:13.801 --> 02:15.567
You can go, Detective.

02:21.842 --> 02:28.013
I have the commissioner's
home number on my desk,
right next to the mayor's.

02:28.749 --> 02:30.616
We can sure do this.

02:33.420 --> 02:36.488
-Ken's secretary,
you like her?
-No.

02:36.490 --> 02:41.527
-She a little afraid of you?
-More than a little,
I hope. Why?

02:41.529 --> 02:45.197
Ask her for a favor.
And don't tell Ken.

02:57.478 --> 02:59.711
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

03:02.249 --> 03:04.449
(ACOUSTIC GUITAR PLAYING)

03:15.029 --> 03:17.396
I was just
in the kitchen, Charlie.

03:18.232 --> 03:19.331
Um...

03:19.333 --> 03:22.334
Did you know
there's nothing to eat?

03:22.603 --> 03:24.536
Like, not a crumb.

03:25.739 --> 03:28.140
Come here, little thing.

03:32.880 --> 03:34.179
Sit.

03:36.717 --> 03:38.951
I know your hunger's real.

03:39.253 --> 03:40.686
So's mine.

03:40.754 --> 03:42.788
So's everybody's.

03:43.257 --> 03:45.557
But you know
what's bigger than that?

03:45.559 --> 03:47.259
Your power.

03:47.861 --> 03:48.727
Look.

03:48.729 --> 03:53.465
Sadie and Katie are using
their power to work
on the dream.

03:53.667 --> 03:56.001
You know what
the dream is, right?

03:56.604 --> 03:58.136
Of course.

03:58.539 --> 04:00.038
Your music.

04:01.041 --> 04:05.377
So tell me, what are you
doing for the dream?

04:06.080 --> 04:07.679
I...

04:08.015 --> 04:10.315
Haven't thought
of anything.

04:12.019 --> 04:13.852
Come look.

04:14.021 --> 04:16.722
Can you see me
on the cover of one of these?

04:16.724 --> 04:18.357
Dressed like this?

04:18.359 --> 04:21.293
I'm gonna meet
record producers,
the best in the biz.

04:21.295 --> 04:26.198
And are they gonna
look at Charlie and go,
"Bigger than the Beatles"?

04:27.368 --> 04:31.370
You don't even know how
important you are to all this.

04:33.007 --> 04:34.139
But you're gonna
figure it out.

04:34.141 --> 04:37.843
-When was the last time
Manson checked in?
-BRUCE: <i> Oh, about a month.</i>

04:37.845 --> 04:40.379
I need you to be just a
little bit more specific.

04:40.381 --> 04:42.547
Uh, uh, yeah, yeah, yeah.
Okay.

04:42.549 --> 04:43.548
Uh... (CLEARS THROAT)

04:43.550 --> 04:44.650
-Hold on.
-Yeah.

04:44.652 --> 04:46.918
Yeah, I wanted to pick up
where we left off
with Gladner.

04:46.920 --> 04:51.590
It's bad vibes, man.
People saying you're the fuzz.

04:52.526 --> 04:54.159
Now, why would anyone
think that?

04:54.161 --> 04:57.496
Streets got
their own thing, my man.

04:57.498 --> 04:58.697
There's...

04:58.699 --> 04:59.131
(GRUNTS)

04:59.133 --> 05:01.667
Crazy whispers in
the concrete.

05:01.669 --> 05:05.404
<i> # Crazy whispers</i>
<i> in the concrete #</i>

05:05.472 --> 05:06.571
(COUGHS)

05:06.573 --> 05:09.675
Hey, do you think that
that would be a good
song title?

05:09.677 --> 05:12.577
<i> -I'm coming over.</i>
-Wait, what?

05:12.579 --> 05:13.812
And if I have to look for you,

05:13.814 --> 05:16.915
I'm gonna teach you a whole
new song about concrete.

05:16.917 --> 05:17.783
Shafe.

05:17.785 --> 05:20.285
You were supposed to get me
an update yesterday.

05:20.287 --> 05:23.322
Yeah, uh, sorry,
I got distracted
with that, uh,

05:23.324 --> 05:24.222
off-the-books thing
we're doing.

05:24.224 --> 05:27.125
Yeah, well, you want
to play the big top, you
got to learn to juggle.

05:27.127 --> 05:32.230
Hey, sorry, got it, uh...
Well, supposed to be
October 11th,

05:32.232 --> 05:33.332
but failed to check in.

05:33.334 --> 05:37.769
Half case of I.W. Harpers
coming your way, but I
need a current address.

05:37.771 --> 05:39.471
Why don't you check
with known associates,

05:39.473 --> 05:42.407
and how about that
Beverly Hills lawyer of his,
Ken Karn?

05:42.409 --> 05:46.311
<i> -You got it.</i>
-Bottoms up,
you Irish bastard.

05:46.313 --> 05:47.546
(CLICKS)

05:47.848 --> 05:53.118
-This a bad time for a favor?
-Depends.
You offering or asking?

05:53.120 --> 05:55.721
-My snitch, Vickery?
-Guitar man.

05:55.723 --> 06:01.226
That's right. Uh, well,
turns out he's been blabbing
about my secret identity.

06:04.098 --> 06:06.531
So you get the play, right?

06:07.368 --> 06:08.367
It only works if you're you.

06:08.369 --> 06:12.471
But on purpose, like,
1,000-yard stare,
psycho-cop scary.

06:12.473 --> 06:16.308
You want to see scary,
keep your foot
right where it is.

06:17.211 --> 06:17.776
(POLICE RADIO STATIC)

06:17.778 --> 06:22.647
DISPATCHER: <i> All units, uh,</i>
<i> 187 at 8856 39th Street,</i>
<i> South Central.</i>

06:22.649 --> 06:23.248
<i> Victim is white female.</i>

06:23.250 --> 06:27.252
-White? That neighborhood?
-Six-William-Nine en route.

06:27.254 --> 06:28.587
<i> -10-4, Six-William-Nine.</i>
-(SIREN WAILS)

06:28.589 --> 06:30.422
Whoa, whoa, we got
to meet Vickery at
10:00 sharp.

06:30.424 --> 06:34.092
Keep a snitch waiting,
it'll make his heart
grow fonder.

06:36.263 --> 06:38.230
(POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

06:42.636 --> 06:44.870
MAN: I told you,
get inside the house!

06:47.841 --> 06:50.375
OFFICER: Husband found her,
called it in.

06:51.445 --> 06:54.179
We got here and found her
around 9:00 am.

06:56.483 --> 06:58.683
Joyce Nankin, 62.

06:58.986 --> 07:02.020
Appears to be
blunt force to the head.

07:08.662 --> 07:13.632
-Where were you before you
came home, Mr. Nankin?
-The studio.

07:13.634 --> 07:18.069
-Oh, you're an artist?
-Dance instructor.

07:21.175 --> 07:22.908
Oh. So you were teaching
at the...

07:22.910 --> 07:24.176
No. No.

07:26.847 --> 07:27.279
It's closed.

07:27.281 --> 07:32.184
-Wednesdays in general or...
-Closed. Completely.

07:32.286 --> 07:34.085
So what were you doing there?

07:36.123 --> 07:38.723
Cleaning up, packing.

07:38.792 --> 07:40.258
Alone?

07:41.328 --> 07:42.561
Yes.

07:42.763 --> 07:48.066
(CLEARS THROAT)
Mr. Nankin, have you...
Have you had any trouble

07:48.068 --> 07:49.601
in the neighborhood?

07:49.603 --> 07:56.741
No problems. Except
we woke up one day in Africa,

07:56.743 --> 08:01.580
with their music and their
sounds and their stink.

08:01.582 --> 08:04.583
Lovely, all of it,
'cause business is booming.

08:04.585 --> 08:06.751
I mean, who wouldn't want
to drive down here to...

08:06.753 --> 08:09.621
To darkest monkey-ville and
learn how to do the box step?

08:09.623 --> 08:16.428
And you people,
you were so, so good
when my car was broken into

08:16.430 --> 08:17.662
and when I got mugged.

08:17.664 --> 08:21.967
You almost got down here
the day that we called you.

08:22.936 --> 08:24.569
And we thank you.

08:25.539 --> 08:27.005
My wife

08:27.908 --> 08:29.174
and I,

08:30.611 --> 08:31.943
we thank you.

08:31.945 --> 08:33.678
MANSON: <i> We got no bread.</i>

08:33.680 --> 08:35.146
You know what I need.

08:35.148 --> 08:36.948
Make it happen.

08:37.551 --> 08:38.950
(MANSON SIGHS)

08:41.255 --> 08:42.921
This is your moment.

08:42.923 --> 08:45.790
You dive into your own
beautiful future

08:46.326 --> 08:49.127
or fall right back into
Mommy and Daddy.

08:52.933 --> 08:54.299
(CAR DOOR OPENS)

08:54.635 --> 08:56.501
KEN: <i> He's crazier than ever.</i>

08:56.503 --> 08:57.736
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

08:57.738 --> 09:01.640
-What else did he say?
-KEN: Besides the fact
that he has my daughter?

09:01.642 --> 09:03.775
You never should have
gone to a cop, Ken.

09:03.777 --> 09:09.347
-Grace was out of her...
-This cop and Grace, that's
the problem, Ken.

09:09.950 --> 09:11.550
Charlie we can deal with.

09:11.552 --> 09:12.217
Charlie's an ant.

09:12.219 --> 09:15.487
All right, he wants to meet
somebody in the music
business?

09:15.489 --> 09:16.321
Whatever. You make it happen.

09:16.323 --> 09:19.958
-He has to give my girl back.
-All right, first you make
Charlie happy,

09:19.960 --> 09:22.427
then you get this
cop to step off.

09:23.797 --> 09:25.397
Look at me.

09:27.234 --> 09:30.068
I'm not the only one
Manson can hurt.

09:30.404 --> 09:32.137
We can't afford this, Kenny.

09:32.139 --> 09:33.505
Not right now.

09:34.174 --> 09:35.507
(SIGHS)

09:36.243 --> 09:38.076
How does this afternoon look?

09:38.512 --> 09:41.046
-This afternoon?
-The fundraiser.

09:41.048 --> 09:44.316
-Oh, my god.
-Get it together, Kenny.

09:44.318 --> 09:45.884
-This is a ball
we do not drop.
-(KNOCKING)

09:45.886 --> 09:49.454
Mr. Karn, I know you
said no interruptions, but
there's an urgent call

09:49.456 --> 09:53.291
from Mr. Bruce Tamminy
from the San Pedro
parole office.

09:53.293 --> 09:55.927
He says it's regarding
your client Charles Manson.

09:55.929 --> 09:58.463
Yeah, put him through, Sheryl.
I'll take care of it.

10:01.401 --> 10:02.200
Bruce. (CHUCKLES)

10:02.202 --> 10:05.103
<i> -Mr. Karn.</i>
-Yeah, no, Ken's out of the
office right now, Bruce,

10:05.105 --> 10:08.640
but, uh, I wanted
to make sure I spoke
to you immediately

10:08.642 --> 10:10.875
about your Mr. Manson.

10:11.311 --> 10:12.944
(SIREN WAILS)

10:13.847 --> 10:15.347
(MOTORCYCLE REVS)

10:15.716 --> 10:17.082
(SIREN STOPS)

10:20.754 --> 10:23.755
(POP MUSIC PLAYING
ON THE RADIO)

10:29.863 --> 10:32.731
OFFICER: Hey!
MAN: Well, hey, man!

10:32.733 --> 10:33.832
What did I tell you?

10:33.834 --> 10:36.701
Told you to stay away
from the front of the store.

10:36.703 --> 10:38.870
-Get out.
Get out into the street.
-WOMAN: Relax!

10:38.872 --> 10:42.007
MAN: Just relax, man.
OFFICER: Put your
cigarette out.

11:02.896 --> 11:04.529
Thank you.

11:04.798 --> 11:06.564
OFFICER: Shut your mouth.
MAN: Come on.

11:06.566 --> 11:08.667
OFFICER: You're going
to jail today.

11:08.669 --> 11:10.101
What I told you.

11:10.103 --> 11:11.369
Move on.

11:12.606 --> 11:14.205
-Hey!
-(GASPS)

11:14.441 --> 11:15.073
Unbelievable.

11:15.075 --> 11:17.375
-You kids just come in here...
-Ow! Stop!

11:17.377 --> 11:19.244
And grab whatever you want
all the time.

11:19.246 --> 11:22.113
(GRUNTS) Let go of me. Let go!

11:22.115 --> 11:25.216
Oh, no, no, no, no.
Stop, no cops, come on.

11:25.218 --> 11:27.252
Ow! Stop it!

11:27.254 --> 11:28.486
Stop!

11:29.189 --> 11:31.089
-Let go of me.
-Shut up.

11:31.391 --> 11:33.358
You're hurting me.

11:33.927 --> 11:35.293
Aw, baby-jam.

11:35.295 --> 11:39.130
What are you doing?
What's she doing?

11:39.132 --> 11:41.666
-Going to jail is what.
-No.

11:42.169 --> 11:46.538
-Got to bite the hand
that frees you.
-What?

11:47.107 --> 11:49.908
Bite the hand that frees you.

11:51.912 --> 11:53.144
(GRUNTS)

11:53.447 --> 11:54.713
Bitch!

11:56.116 --> 11:57.849
(MOTORCYCLE REVS)

11:59.319 --> 12:00.552
Hey!

12:00.854 --> 12:02.487
Officer! Hey!

12:02.556 --> 12:03.988
(BOTH GRUNT)

12:07.094 --> 12:08.993
(UPBEAT POP MUSIC PLAYING)

12:30.951 --> 12:34.452
-How, um, how'd you...
-You think being
pretty's enough?

12:35.889 --> 12:40.592
You think being a sweet slice
of pie gets you a ticket
to the show?

12:40.594 --> 12:42.026
You like your mommy?

12:42.028 --> 12:43.628
You want to be just like her?

12:43.630 --> 12:47.332
Arctic, dried-up, gin-cured,
slit trench?

12:47.334 --> 12:52.904
-(STAMMERING) No.
-Do what needs to be done,
and stop making it about you.

12:52.906 --> 12:56.641
-Did he... Did he call
the cops on us?
-Don't worry about him.

12:56.643 --> 12:57.542
(ENGINE STARTS)

12:57.544 --> 13:00.211
He didn't see a damn thing.

13:00.514 --> 13:02.680
(UPBEAT POP MUSIC PLAYING)

13:06.353 --> 13:07.852
(GROANING)

13:09.122 --> 13:11.589
SAM: We'll just be...
We'll just be
a couple minutes.

13:11.591 --> 13:14.025
If you want to just
have a seat.

13:18.131 --> 13:19.063
Hodiak.

13:19.065 --> 13:19.964
Husband has brain cancer.

13:19.966 --> 13:22.600
Nothing they can do but
dope him up till it gets him.

13:23.670 --> 13:25.103
(SIGHS)

13:25.639 --> 13:27.172
(SETS DOWN BOTTLE)

13:30.377 --> 13:34.112
-Can you do that?
-I don't know, can I?

13:34.481 --> 13:37.749
-What is it?
-It's a birthday card.

13:39.886 --> 13:43.855
SHAFE: So you make the
husband as the doer?
HODIAK: I do indeed.

13:43.857 --> 13:44.522
(ENGINE STOPS)

13:44.524 --> 13:46.791
Not seeing a whole lot
of evidence.

13:46.793 --> 13:49.727
Well, domestic homicide,
you usually don't.

13:49.729 --> 13:51.696
It's usually he said/she dead.

13:51.698 --> 13:55.466
-So what are we doing here?
-Best milkshake in town.

13:55.468 --> 13:58.036
We're stepping off the
suspect for a milkshake?

13:58.038 --> 14:00.104
No, we're gonna let him
stew a little bit,

14:00.106 --> 14:03.141
give him some alone time
with his conscience.

14:04.511 --> 14:07.445
Legs spread.
Hands on the wall.

14:08.849 --> 14:11.749
And why in the hell
should I do that?

14:13.520 --> 14:15.820
I'm lonely.
You're my best shot.

14:15.822 --> 14:20.158
-You got to buy me
dinner first.
-I don't eat with you people.

14:22.696 --> 14:23.561
(LAUGHS)

14:23.563 --> 14:24.929
It's my first beat.

14:24.931 --> 14:26.297
1947.

14:27.634 --> 14:28.766
-(PHONE RINGS)
-Change much?

14:28.768 --> 14:31.202
I think the coffee's from '47.

14:31.204 --> 14:32.637
That hasn't changed.

14:32.639 --> 14:34.606
Sam, phone.

14:36.209 --> 14:38.309
(REPORTER SPEAKING ON TV)

14:38.311 --> 14:38.610
Hodiak.

14:38.612 --> 14:41.346
NEWSCASTER:
<i> ...marched across the Potomac</i>
<i> and amassed at the Pentagon,</i>

14:41.348 --> 14:42.313
<i> resulting in</i>
<i> a full-scale riot.</i>

14:42.315 --> 14:48.052
I had Charmain check.
The Nankins have been the
victims of crime zero times.

14:48.054 --> 14:51.756
So that lie was
incredibly stupid.

14:51.758 --> 14:55.059
Most murders, you're not
exactly dealing with
Goldfinger.

14:55.061 --> 14:58.529
SAM: Very sorry, Leo.
My aunt had
the exact same thing.

14:58.531 --> 15:00.865
The pills just
killed her appetite.

15:00.867 --> 15:02.467
Except for one thing.

15:02.736 --> 15:04.636
Vanilla milkshake.

15:09.009 --> 15:10.608
SHAFE: <i> How are you today?</i>

15:10.677 --> 15:13.077
You mind if I ask
you a few questions?

15:13.146 --> 15:14.545
(SCOFFS)

15:14.915 --> 15:16.814
Nothing too heavy. Just a few.

15:16.816 --> 15:18.516
She was a real looker,
your missus.

15:18.518 --> 15:21.352
MGM dancer in the '30s?
Big deal back in the day.

15:21.354 --> 15:23.721
I think I saw her
with Fred Astaire.

15:23.723 --> 15:25.657
You in the movies too, Leo?

15:25.659 --> 15:30.194
-No. No, I didn't
get that far.
-Why not?

15:31.131 --> 15:33.431
Just not good enough.

15:33.433 --> 15:36.167
Ah, not good enough.

15:36.169 --> 15:39.003
Bet you heard that a few
times, huh, Leo?

15:39.005 --> 15:40.805
LEE: <i> You sure you're a cop?</i>

15:40.807 --> 15:43.574
Oh. I just need a trim.

15:43.944 --> 15:45.977
Or you're a narc.

15:46.146 --> 15:47.145
(CHUCKLES)

15:47.147 --> 15:49.547
Anyway, uh,
between 7:15 and 8:15,

15:49.549 --> 15:51.683
Mr. Nankin's car
was in the driveway.

15:51.685 --> 15:55.386
And you saw him,
7:30, 7:45 right out front?

15:55.388 --> 16:00.725
-He was on his porch, smoking.
-Did you say good morning?

16:00.727 --> 16:04.429
He never so much
looked me in the eye,
me or my family.

16:04.431 --> 16:08.366
And that wife of his,
God rest but...

16:08.735 --> 16:11.436
She didn't have
a Christian bone in her body.

16:11.438 --> 16:15.273
Afternoon, Ms. Lee.
May we speak with you?

16:15.275 --> 16:17.241
Uh, in a second, guys.
We're just in the middle of...

16:17.243 --> 16:19.510
We know what you're doing,
Officer, and it's now over.

16:19.512 --> 16:23.614
-Go inside, baby.
-We're investigating
a murder here.

16:24.617 --> 16:25.583
Ma'am...

16:25.585 --> 16:26.551
Excuse me.

