32:23.842 --> 32:24.875
or telling me to dress better.

32:24.877 --> 32:27.344
One of the Nation's
objectives is for all Negroes

32:27.346 --> 32:29.413
to leave the
United slave States

32:29.415 --> 32:31.615
and repopulate
our native Africa.

32:31.617 --> 32:33.216
But when you imprison me
without reason...

32:33.218 --> 32:34.985
-Without reason?
-...to achieve your objective

32:34.987 --> 32:36.820
despite the suffering
you inflicted on me...

32:36.822 --> 32:38.355
You were interfering
with a police investigation.

32:38.357 --> 32:39.423
I see now that
my true path lies

32:39.425 --> 32:40.958
not in flight from
this country...

32:40.960 --> 32:43.126
Oh, Bunchy, I've known you
since you were 11 years old.

32:43.128 --> 32:44.728
My true path lies
in changing this country

32:44.730 --> 32:46.163
because I'm not a pacifist.

32:46.165 --> 32:47.864
No, you're a crook
in a new costume.

32:47.866 --> 32:50.033
You are a living lie.

32:50.703 --> 32:55.706
I am the truth who
will burn your world
to the ground.

32:57.376 --> 33:00.344
Does this mean
I really get to keep the tie?

33:00.546 --> 33:02.779
Watch your back, Hodiak.

33:17.162 --> 33:18.762
Jimmy C.

33:21.000 --> 33:22.065
Is it my turn in the box?

33:22.067 --> 33:24.334
Are you gonna, what,
sweat me for an apology?

33:24.336 --> 33:26.503
This is how it goes.
When I am closing a case,

33:26.505 --> 33:27.671
you never, ever do that again!

33:27.673 --> 33:29.339
Closing a case?
Is that what you call that?

33:29.341 --> 33:31.008
-The guy did it!
-The guy had rights!

33:31.010 --> 33:32.109
-Not today.
-Back up.

33:32.111 --> 33:33.877
-What?
-Back up.

33:36.749 --> 33:38.515
You think all you did
was lean on a perp?

33:38.517 --> 33:40.717
When you haul in
an innocent man...

33:40.719 --> 33:41.151
Bunchy?

33:41.153 --> 33:42.285
On some trumped-up
obstruction beef

33:42.287 --> 33:43.854
you know
he had nothing to do with...

33:43.856 --> 33:44.988
Child, he didn't know that.

33:44.990 --> 33:47.958
He's just a dumb spade
to you, right?

33:47.960 --> 33:50.127
-Oh...
-Yeah, doesn't know nothing
about nothing.

33:50.129 --> 33:52.496
-Grow up.
-Easiest target in the world.

33:52.498 --> 33:53.797
I was shaking him loose.

33:53.799 --> 33:54.364
You hold him overnight.

33:54.366 --> 33:56.366
You dump a crime spree on him
he had nothing to do with.

33:56.368 --> 33:58.435
Would you pull any of that
if he were white?

33:58.437 --> 34:00.971
Would I pound
the fear of God into some mope

34:00.973 --> 34:02.773
I needed to bend
if he was white?

34:02.775 --> 34:03.840
Yes.

34:03.842 --> 34:05.742
I did, for you.

34:05.744 --> 34:06.843
(CHUCKLES)

34:06.845 --> 34:09.312
If you think
those things are the same,

34:09.314 --> 34:12.382
maybe we can't do this,
you and me.

34:12.384 --> 34:13.683
And you helped me out,

34:13.685 --> 34:15.085
and I want to help you
find that girl,

34:15.087 --> 34:18.355
but I will not do the job
the way you do.

34:18.357 --> 34:21.024
You don't even know
what the job is.

34:24.129 --> 34:25.429
You know what?

34:25.431 --> 34:27.164
Give me a ride home.

34:27.166 --> 34:28.065
Excuse me?

34:28.067 --> 34:31.501
We get through this
or past it.

34:32.638 --> 34:34.137
You know, like,
literally half the time,

34:34.139 --> 34:37.307
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

34:45.417 --> 34:47.517
Oh, hey, Howard.

34:48.353 --> 34:50.587
I'm good. You?

34:52.224 --> 34:53.457
Huh?

34:54.093 --> 34:55.392
Come on.

34:55.994 --> 34:57.360
She did?

34:57.663 --> 34:58.528
Seriously?

34:58.530 --> 35:01.431
Well, the ladies, huh?
What are you gonna do?

35:05.771 --> 35:07.471
Him I like.

35:07.673 --> 35:09.706
-KRISTIN: And the baby
does this...
-Hey.

35:09.708 --> 35:13.343
Hey, honey.
Have a nice chat with Howard?

35:13.512 --> 35:14.744
Always.

35:15.481 --> 35:16.746
Hi.

35:17.416 --> 35:19.049
You're home early.

35:21.186 --> 35:22.452
Mwah.

35:22.588 --> 35:23.987
Yeah, this is Hodiak.

35:23.989 --> 35:25.021
Uh, we work together.

35:25.023 --> 35:26.556
-Sam.
-Kristin.

35:26.558 --> 35:28.658
Nice to meet you.

35:28.660 --> 35:30.560
And then who is this?

35:30.729 --> 35:31.528
Bernadette.

35:31.530 --> 35:33.330
Bernadette? My favorite saint.

35:33.332 --> 35:36.800
Well, I'm not too sure
that's her career path.

35:36.802 --> 35:39.069
-Mmm-mmm.
-(LAUGHS)

35:39.938 --> 35:41.805
(BERNADETTE COOING)

35:44.009 --> 35:45.242
Yes.

35:45.444 --> 35:47.043
-Subtle.
-(DOOR CLOSES)

35:47.045 --> 35:48.845
Don't lead a subtle life.
Thought you ought to know.

35:48.847 --> 35:53.316
I don't unless we are going to
keep on looking for Emma.

35:56.855 --> 35:58.955
Then I guess you do.

36:00.792 --> 36:02.225
(CAR DOOR OPENS)

36:02.995 --> 36:04.928
CUTLER: <i> So, Sam,</i>
<i> this thing with Walt.</i>

36:04.930 --> 36:06.763
<i> I talked to my brother-in-law</i>
<i> at Pendleton.</i>

36:06.765 --> 36:09.366
The thing I don't get is
how he just got out.

36:09.368 --> 36:10.233
I mean,
my brother-in-law said,

36:10.235 --> 36:13.103
"The only way you ever
get sent stateside is

36:13.105 --> 36:13.970
"if one of your parents
is dying."

36:13.972 --> 36:17.607
And, I mean, it takes
letters and doctors and all...

36:19.444 --> 36:20.844
(EXHALES)

36:26.351 --> 36:28.285
SAM: Opal.

36:28.687 --> 36:29.920
Officer.

36:36.762 --> 36:41.064
You sent the letter, didn't
you? To get him back.

36:41.066 --> 36:42.332
Said you were what?

36:42.334 --> 36:43.300
Sick? Dying?

36:43.302 --> 36:47.237
Which one of your barfly
friends did you get to
play the doctor?

36:47.940 --> 36:48.505
(GLASS SHATTERS)

36:48.507 --> 36:51.408
Our son is AWOL
from a combat zone.

36:51.410 --> 36:53.810
He's a deserter.
He could go to prison.

36:53.812 --> 36:55.045
You too.

36:55.247 --> 36:57.113
You're in a real
pickle there, Officer.

36:57.115 --> 36:58.648
You gonna turn me in?

36:58.650 --> 37:01.585
No. You're gonna do
what's right.

37:02.020 --> 37:03.553
You're gonna turn him in.

37:03.555 --> 37:04.988
I won't have to.

37:05.724 --> 37:06.556
They'll come for him.

37:06.558 --> 37:08.959
You have no idea
what you've done.

37:09.962 --> 37:11.194
Walt?

37:25.143 --> 37:27.911
So his secretary said

37:28.513 --> 37:31.514
Ken had gotten nine phone
calls from Manson.

37:31.516 --> 37:34.551
She said, as far as she knows,
Ken never returned.

37:34.553 --> 37:36.386
But he got the messages.

37:36.388 --> 37:37.520
SAM: Hmm.

37:37.522 --> 37:41.758
Well, here's the log,
just dates and times.

37:42.327 --> 37:45.662
I'm having so much trouble
understanding this,

37:45.664 --> 37:47.530
why Ken is...

37:47.633 --> 37:49.299
(LAUGHS)

37:49.768 --> 37:52.836
-This isn't...
-Sam Hodiak wears glasses.

37:52.838 --> 37:55.405
-I don't know
what you're talking about.
-No? Mmm.

37:55.407 --> 37:58.575
-Invisible.
-(CHUCKLES)

37:59.411 --> 38:00.710
Okay.

38:00.946 --> 38:03.046
What about Ken?

38:05.317 --> 38:11.054
I don't remember the last time
I understood him.

38:12.391 --> 38:14.024
<i> He's a sphinx.</i>

38:18.230 --> 38:23.667
<i> I can tell you</i>
<i> exactly what he'll say</i>
<i> in any given situation,</i>

38:24.369 --> 38:32.208
<i> what music he'll like,</i>
<i> tie he'll pick,</i>
<i> candidate he will vote for.</i>

38:32.678 --> 38:33.276
(CHUCKLES)

38:33.278 --> 38:37.981
But I've never had any idea
what he was thinking ever.

38:38.350 --> 38:40.550
Why did you marry him?

38:42.120 --> 38:43.486
Hot summer.

38:45.390 --> 38:47.424
You were long gone.

38:52.497 --> 38:54.898
My dad liked him.

38:55.667 --> 38:58.568
So, not strong reasons.

39:00.972 --> 39:02.372
I got pregnant.

39:03.141 --> 39:05.942
-That's a good reason.
-(LAUGHS)

39:05.944 --> 39:07.477
So what about you?

39:07.746 --> 39:10.814
Why did you marry, you know...

39:10.882 --> 39:12.115
-Opal?
-Yeah.

39:12.117 --> 39:12.982
-Opal.
-Why did you marry her?

39:12.984 --> 39:17.187
(LAUGHS) I can't remember.
I can't remember.

39:18.323 --> 39:22.225
I can't remember.

39:26.198 --> 39:29.399
Are you sure
I can't get you a drink?

39:32.137 --> 39:34.204
(SIGHS)

39:34.206 --> 39:35.905
Pretty sure.

39:36.875 --> 39:39.743
You don't drink anymore,
do you?

39:40.011 --> 39:45.315
Drinking, I don't tend
to make the best decisions.

39:57.129 --> 39:58.828
(DOOR CLOSES)

39:58.830 --> 40:00.196
Half.

40:01.833 --> 40:05.535
I get my girl out of here,
you get the other half.

40:05.537 --> 40:07.036
And Hal knows I'm here.

40:07.038 --> 40:11.307
You do anything, anything,
and it's over for you.

40:11.309 --> 40:12.776
You hear me?

40:12.878 --> 40:14.277
Anything?

40:15.347 --> 40:17.046
Shit, Ken...

40:17.249 --> 40:19.149
We're not enemies.

40:19.818 --> 40:21.484
We never were.

40:21.653 --> 40:23.119
You're the one who forgot.

40:23.121 --> 40:28.758
You're the one who, when
I called and called and
called, wouldn't answer.

40:52.951 --> 40:54.584
Charlie?

40:58.290 --> 40:59.823
(CHUCKLES)

41:03.361 --> 41:04.828
Charlie?

41:11.236 --> 41:13.636
Come back later, Cherry-pop.

41:14.473 --> 41:15.972
I'm busy.

41:20.679 --> 41:22.178
(KNOB TURNS)

41:25.851 --> 41:27.951
You do as I say now.

41:35.126 --> 41:37.327
It's all right, Ken.

41:39.064 --> 41:41.097
It's all right.

41:45.203 --> 41:46.503
Be free.

41:46.938 --> 41:49.739
Do you remember
how free we were?

41:49.741 --> 41:55.278
I showed you
you could finally be
who you were.

41:55.580 --> 41:59.516
So sweet,
those nights of ours.

42:00.919 --> 42:04.020
So sweet, my Kenny-Ken.
